radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is enlarged measuring 7 mm proximally and more dilated distally to 1.4 cm. There is an appendicolith at the transition point as well as periappendiceal stranding. No evidence of perforation. The base of the lungs are clear bilaterally. The liver enhances homogeneously with no focal lesion identified. There is no intrahepatic biliary dilatation. The portal vein is patent. The gallbladder is without radiopaque cholelithiasis. The pancreas, spleen, and bilateral adrenal glands are unremarkable. Kidneys present symmetric nephrograms and excretion of contrast with no evidence of hydronephrosis. The stomach, duodenum, and loops of small bowel are unremarkable. The colon is unremarkable. No evidence of obstruction or abdominal free fluid. The abdominal aorta is normal in caliber without aneurysmal dilatation. There is no retroperitoneal or mesenteric adenopathy. The bladder is moderately well distended. Distal ureters are opacified and within normal limits. Prostate gland and seminal vesicles are normal in appearance. There is no inguinal or pelvic adenopathy. There is no suspicious lytic or blastic lesion.
